Cell.Text: [S] S|<<Shared>> My sister Gerdur runs the mill in Riverwood, just up the road. I'm sure she'd help you out.
[S] I was hoping you'd change your mind. Come on. I'm heading to Riverwood, just up the road. My sister Gerdur will help us out.

Node.Caption: MQ102RalofIntroBlocking: What now?

Cell.Text: G|All right. If I make it back to Windhelm, I'll make sure Ulfric knows how you helped me. | Skyrim needs people like you, if we ever hope to regain our freedom from the damned Empire. Good luck.

Node.Caption: MQ102RalofIntroA1: I think I'll make my own way from here.

Cell.Text: [S] GS|<<Shared>> You know, you should come to Windhelm with me and join the fight to free Skyrim. You've seen the true face of the Empire here today. | If anyone knows what the coming of the dragon means, Ulfric will.
[S] G|Keep an eye out for Imperials. They still hold this whole area. As long as we don't do anything stupid, we should be alright.

Node.Caption: MQ102RaolofIntroA2: Sounds good. Let's go.

S|Ralof? How do you know him?
[S] Like I said, I'm glad to help in any way I can. Help yourself to whatever you need, within reason.
Ralof said you could help me out.
<<Shared>> If you really are Ralof's friend, I'll be glad to help you. But you didn't answer my question - how do you know him?

Node.Caption: MQ102BRiverwoodHelpTopic: Can you help me out?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> If you really are Ralof's friend, I'll be glad to help you. But you didn't answer my question - how do you know him?

Node.Caption: MQ102GerdurHelpA1: He's a friend. He promised you could help.

Cell.Text: You did? We heard that Ulfric was captured... | ... no, sorry, but in times like these I can't just take the word of a stranger who wanders into town claiming to be my brother's friend.

Node.Caption: MQ102GerdurHelpA2: We escaped from the Imperials together.

Cell.Text: Just head north, you can't miss it. It's the capital of Whiterun hold. | Jarl Balgruuf still hasn't declared for one side or the other, so at least you won't run into any Imperials along the way.
Cross the river and then head north. You'll see Whiterun on its hill as you pass the falls.

Node.Caption: MQ102BWhiterunTopicTopic: How do I get to Whiterun from here?

Cell.Text: The Empire may have been good for Skyrim once upon a time, but those days are long past. | Banning the worship of Talos was the last straw. Imperial Justiciars everywhere, dragging people off for honoring our own gods! | I'm glad Ralof is helping drive them out of here. If I was a bit younger, I might have joined the fight myself.
I've got enough to worry about, taking care of my family. I don't concern myself with such matters.

Node.Caption: MQ102BCivilWarTopic: What do you think about the war?

Cell.Text: So you saw a dragon, did you? Tell me, what was it like? As big as a house?

Node.Caption: MQ102HodDragonTopic

Cell.Text: [S] G|Sure, sure. It's just, you know, not every day I meet someone who's laid eyes on a dragon.

Node.Caption: MQ102HodDragonA1: I really don't want to talk about it.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Well I'll be! That'd be a sight to see. | Not that I actually want to see one, understand. I hope that dragon stays far away from here.

Node.Caption: MQ102HodDragonA2: Much bigger than that. As big as the inn.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Don't even say such things! I hope that dragon stays away from Riverwood. We don't need that kind of trouble.

Node.Caption: MQ102HodDragonA3: Maybe you'll see one yourself soon. Helgen isn't that far from here.

Cell.Text: G|I'm glad to help in any way I can. | But I need your help. We need your help.
[S] G|<<Shared>> Here's a key to the house. Stay as long as you like. If there's anything else you need, just let me know.

Node.Caption: MQ102GerdurHelpForcegreetTopic

Cell.Text: S|Well... maybe not. Dragons haven't been seen in Skyrim for an age or more. | But wherever that dragon came from, and whatever it wants, Ulfric will get to the bottom of it. You can count on that. | Besides, you have your own score to settle with the Empire now. And with that dragon.

Node.Caption: MQ102RalofJoinStormcloaksA1: You think Ulfric knows where that dragon came from?

Cell.Text: Damn right. Just like all true sons of Skryim should.
Damn right. You don't have to be a Nord to fight for Skyrim's freedom.
How do I join the Stormcloaks?

Ulfric's capital is Windhelm, northeast of here. You'll want to talk to Galmar Stone-Fist, Ulfric's right hand man. He handles the new recruits. | I'll be sure to put in a good word if I get to Windhelm ahead of you.

Node.Caption: MQ102BRalofJoinStormcloaksTopic: You really think I should join up with Ulfric Stormcloak?

Cell.Text: [S] You should come to Windhelm with me and join the fight to free Skyrim. You've seen the true face of the Empire here today. | If anyone knows what the coming of the dragon means, Ulfric will.

Node.Caption: MQ102BRalofJoinStormcloaksA0

Cell.Text: G|I hope so. Skyrim needs people like you to fight for her freedom. | Come on, we'd better get moving.

Node.Caption: MQ102RalofJoinStormcloaksYes: You make a good case. Maybe I will go to Windhelm.

Cell.Text: G|Yeah, sure, I understand. No need to decide now. | But I know that after you think about what you saw today, you'll realize that Skyrim deserves to be free.

Node.Caption: MQ102RalofJoinStormcloaksNo: I'll have to think about it.

Cell.Text: G|<<Shared>> That's where I'm headed. You can come with me if you want.

Node.Caption: MQ102BRalofIntroA0

Cell.Text: A dragon?! In Helgen? That's impossible. Dragons don't exist... they're just stories from long ago...

Node.Caption: MQ102GerdurHelpB1: A dragon attacked Helgen and destroyed it. Ralof and I escaped together.

Cell.Text: G|I'm sorry to turn you away. I hope you understand. | By the way, if you're looking for work, Hod can always use help at the mill.

Node.Caption: MQ102GerdurHelpB2: Never mind.

Cell.Text: I don't know why... but I actually believe you. You've got the look of someone who's just seen a dragon. | Things just go from bad to worse. First the war, now dragons... what's this world coming to?

Node.Caption: MQ102GerdurHelpC1: It is true. Ralof will tell you the same thing.

Cell.Text: Hilde was going on about something flying up the valley... now that you mention it, I think she did say it was a dragon... | I didn't pay much attention... she's always worked up about something or other...

Node.Caption: MQ102GerdurHelpC2: That dragon flew off this way. I'm surprised you didn't see it.

Cell.Text: [S] The Jarl needs to know if there's a dragon on the loose. Riverwood is defenseless... | We need to get word to Jarl Balgruuf in Whiterun to send whatever troops he can. If you'll do that for me, I'll be in your debt.

Node.Caption: MQ102GerdurHelpD1

Cell.Text: There's something you could do for me. For all of us here.

Node.Caption: MQ102GerdurHelpD0: Is there something else?

Cell.Text: Jarl Balgruuf? I don't mean to be disrespectful, as he's ruled Whiterun Hold well for years, but he seems in over his head now. | He's been trying to stay out of the war, but it can't last. He's going to have to pick a side. I'm afraid he's going to make the wrong choice.

Node.Caption: MQ102BJarlBalgruufTopic: What can you tell me about the Jarl?

Cell.Text: [S] I wouldn't say that. But he and Ulfric have been at odds for years, and I'm afraid Balgruuf will end up siding with the Empire because of it. | But it's hard to believe that even Balgruuf would choose Elisif over Ulfric.

Node.Caption: MQ102BJarlBalgruufA1: Why? Is he loyal to the Empire?

Cell.Text: Of course. Ulfric's cause is just. It's time for Skyrim to rid itself of the Empire.

Node.Caption: MQ102BJarlBalgruufB1: You support the Stormcloaks, then?

Cell.Text: I suppose she's Jarl Elisif now. She married High King Torygg just before Ulfric killed him. The Empire supports her claim to be High Queen. | I don't really have anything against her - not her fault that her husband Torygg was bought and paid for by the Empire. | But she's nothing but a puppet for the Empire now, with her husband Torygg dead. Ulfric will make sure she never takes the throne as High Queen.

Node.Caption: MQ102BElisifTopic: Who's Elisif?

Cell.Text: Some say murdered, but it was a lawful challenge in the old way. | Ulfric called him out as a traitor to Skyrim, and killed him in single combat. | If Torygg couldn't defend his throne, he had no business being High King.

Node.Caption: MQ102BElisifA1: Ulfric killed the High King?

Cell.Text: No, not until the Moot meets to choose another. And it won't meet until one side or the other wins the war. | Don't worry, though. Ulfric is our rightful High King. He'll drive out the Empire and Skyrim will have peace at last.

Node.Caption: MQ102BElisifA2: So there's no High King now?
